## Git and GitHub — do nothing unless the user explicitly asks

**The #1 mistake:** treating “sync” or “upload” as permission to run **git** commands.

| User said | Agent may do | Agent must NOT do |
|-----------|--------------|-------------------|
| “sync”, “upload”, “push to Surface” | **scp scripts only** (`sync-to-pc.sh`, `sync-to-dgx.ps1`, etc.) | `git push`, `git pull`, `git fetch`, merge `upstream`, open PRs |
| “commit” | `git add` + `git commit` (local only) | `git push` unless user also says push |
| “push to GitHub” | User does it (agent has no GitHub SSH key) | Any `git push` / `gh` write |

After the `.env` leak, the user **removed the agent SSH key from GitHub**. Never assume GitHub write access.

**DGX and Surface are the same project folder on two machines** — keep them aligned with **sync scripts over SSH**, not with git remotes or upstream.

## DGX ↔ Surface file copy (scp) — auto-run after edits

**User permission:** After every create/edit/delete in this repo, **run the correct scp sync script yourself** (do not ask the user to run it). This is **not** git — never use `git push` / `git pull` / `upstream` for machine sync.

| You edited on | Run automatically |
|---------------|-------------------|
| **DGX** — DGX-owned files (docs, README, Pitch Deck) | `bash scripts/sync-to-pc.sh` |
| **DGX** — `src/` (DGX was sole editor; lock if needed) | `bash scripts/sync-to-pc.sh --include-src` |
| **Surface** — PC-owned files (`src/`, scripts, roadmaps) | `.\scripts\sync-to-dgx.ps1` |
| **Surface** — need DGX docs/scripts | `.\scripts\sync-from-dgx.ps1` |

From DGX, Surface sync can run via SSH if you are on DGX but changed Surface-owned files through remote commands.

Say **“copied to Surface”** / **“copied to DGX”** in chat — never say “git push” for scp sync.

**Still forbidden without explicit user ask:** `git push`, `git pull`, `git fetch`, merge `upstream`, PRs, GitHub publish.

## After DGX-owned changes

Run automatically: `bash scripts/sync-to-pc.sh` (add `--include-src` only when DGX owned `src/` edits).

## After Surface-owned changes

Run automatically on Surface: `.\scripts\sync-to-dgx.ps1`. Respect single-writer rules for `src/`; do not overwrite Surface `src/` from DGX without lock/sync rules.
